The paper proposes a new framework for secure and robust consensus in blockchain-based IoT networks using machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses supervised machine learning algorithms for outlier detection, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the implementation of the framework on the Hyperledger Fabric platform, which falls under the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with IoT networks, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes a consensus protocol for the blockchain-based IoT network, which falls under the category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
